d on Saturday – and the highest 24-hour tally to date in the country. Health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said in a statement on Sunday evening (3 May), that a further eight people have died from the virus, taking total deaths to 131. He added that a total of 245,747 people have been tested, with 15,061 people tested in the past 24 hours. Mkhize said that more than 7.2 million South Africans have been screened. Read: South Africa’s new lockdown rules face major legal challenges 